A sales assistant, Stanley Mikel, yesterday appeared at an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly selling adulterated alcoholic drinks. He pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Inspector Mathew Akhaluode said Mikel committed the offence on April 17, at Oshodi Market, Lagos. “Mikel was caught while adulterating Seaman Schnapps, Regal Dry Gin and Lord’s Dry Gin, all alcoholic drinks, with the intention of selling them to the public,’’ he said. Magistrate O.O. Fagbohun granted the defendant  N100,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She adjourned till June 7.